  "id": "3c9b380b-b530-46d8-b529-b31cdd0ee3a0",
  "content": [
    {
      "variant": "main",
      "html": "<h4>Activity</h4>\n<br>\n<br>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-desmos-gc\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\"></div>\n<br>\n<br>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"Reveal1\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-content\">\n    <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\">\n      <li>\n        Use the graphing tool above or technology outside this course to graph the following linear functions. Use a different color for each:\n        <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\" type=\"a\">\n          <li>\\(\n            f(x)=3x\\)\n          </li>\n          <li>\\(\n            f(x)=2x\\)\n          </li>\n          <li>\\(f(x)=x\\)</li>\n        </ol>\n      </li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-prompt\">\n    <p>Then select the <strong>Solution</strong> button to compare your work.\n    </p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-content\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-wait-for-event=\"Reveal1\">\n  <p>Compare your answers:</p>\n  <p><img src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/cda29d6b099c68a91921f0878fbd1f6c1b07df31\" width=\"300\"></p>\n</div>\n<br>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-content-id=\"3c91a7e0-da6a-461f-ad3a-cc0cab242354\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\" start=\"2\">\n      <li>What do you notice about the slopes of lines \\(a\\), \\(b\\), and \\(c\\) as the number gets larger?</li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>As the coefficient increases, the line gets steeper.</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<br>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-desmos-gc\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\"></div>\n<br>\n<br>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"Reveal2\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-content\">\n    <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\" start=\"3\">\n      <li>Now, graph lines \\(d\\) and \\(e\\) on the same graph as \\(a\\)&ndash;\\(c\\), but use different colors.</li>\n      <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\" start=\"4\" type=\"a\">\n        <li>\\(f(x)=\\frac12 x\\;\\)</li>\n        <li>\\(\n          f(x)=\\frac13 x\\;\\)\n        </li>\n      </ol>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-prompt\">\n    <p>Then select the <strong>Solution</strong> button to compare your work.\n    </p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-content\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-wait-for-event=\"Reveal2\">\n  <p>Compare your answers:</p>\n  <p><img src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/69001fbe0aab36bc2660cf325e33ea2b9ee76de7\" width=\"300\"></p>\n</div>\n<br>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-content-id=\"fa3e6253-73ee-4fac-a6dc-cd51cd6ae753\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\" start=\"4\">\n      <li>How does line \\(d\\) compare to line \\(b\\)? What can you say about the lines when \\(m&lt;1\\)?</li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>As the coefficient gets smaller, the line is less steep.</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End -->\n<br>\n<br>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"Reveal1\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-content\">\n    <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\" start=\"5\">\n      <li>Now graph lines \\(f\\), \\(g\\), and \\(h\\) on the same coordinate grid as \\(a\\)&ndash;\\(e\\), but use different colors.</li>\n    </ol>\n    <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\">\n      <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\" start=\"6\" type=\"a\">\n        <li>\\(\n          f(x)=-\\frac12 x\\;\\)\n        </li>\n        <li>\\(f(x)=-x\\)</li>\n        <li>\\(f(x)=-2x\\)<br>\n          <br>\n        </li>\n      </ol>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-prompt\">\n    <p> Then select the <strong>Solution</strong> button to compare your work.\n    </p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<br>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-content\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-wait-for-event=\"Reveal1\">\n  <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n  <p><img alt=\"This graph shows seven versions of the function, f of x = x on an x, y coordinate plane. The x-axis runs from negative 8 to 8. The y-axis runs from negative 8 to 8. Seven multi-colored lines run through the point (0, 0). Starting with the lines in the top right quadrant and moving clockwise, the first line is f of x = 3 times x and has a slope of 3, the next line is f of x = 2 times x which has a slope of 2, the next line is f of x = x which has a slope of 1, the next line is f of x = x divided by 2 which has a slope of .5. The last line in this quadrant is f of x = x divided by 3 which has a slope of one third x. In the bottom right quadrant moving clockwise, the first line is f of x = negative x divided by 2, which has a slope of negative one half, the middle line is f of x = negative x which has a slope of negative 1, and the last line is f of x = negative 2 times x which has a slope of  negative 2.\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/c022489323343d3f67bbc9b025766d0cc7fbe1b2\" width=\"300\"></p>\n</div>\n<br>\n<br>\n<!--Text Entry Interaction Start -->\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-input\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-content-id=\"a510ee97-b071-4c24-8e40-0a27d0fde623\" data-fire-event=\"eventShow\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-content\">\n    <ol class=\"os-raise-noindent\" start=\"6\">\n      <li>What changed with these functions? How did this change their graphs?</li>\n    </ol>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-prompt\">\n    <p>Enter your answer here:</p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-input-ack\">\n    <p>Compare your answer:</p>\n    <p>There is a negative coefficient. This reflected the positive version of the line over the x-axis</p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<!--Interaction End --><br>\n<p>In the equation \\(f(x)=mx\\), the \\(m\\) is acting as the <span class=\"os-raise-ib-tooltip\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-store=\"glossary-tooltip\">vertical stretch</span> or <span class=\"os-raise-ib-tooltip\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-store=\"glossary-tooltip\">vertical compression</span> of the identity function. When \\(m\\) is negative, there is also a <span class=\"os-raise-ib-tooltip\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-store=\"glossary-tooltip\">vertical reflection</span> of the graph.</p>\n<p>Multiplying the equation of \\(f(x)=x\\) by \\(m\\) stretches the graph of \\(f\\) by a factor of \\(m\\) units if \\(m&gt;1\\) and compresses the graph of \\(f\\) by a factor of \\(m\\) units if \\(0&lt;m&lt;1\\). This means the larger the absolute value of \\(m\\), the steeper the slope.</p>\n<h4>Video: Identifying Vertical Stretches and Compressions</h4>\n<p>Watch the following video to learn more about vertical stretches and compressions.</p>\n<video controls=\"true\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\" width=\"550\">\n  <source src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/ab2d0745a29cce32d6c39a82461fc1d15be37057\">\n  <track default=\"true\" kind=\"captions\" label=\"On\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/b8785f2e173176360bdf2f05e88af8014891800f\" srclang=\"en_us\">https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/ab2d0745a29cce32d6c39a82461fc1d15be37057\n</video>"
    }
